cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a novel scheme for UAV-enabled communications, which involves wireless networking and communication between the UAV and ground nodes. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the trade-off between file caching cost and file retrieval cost, which can be analyzed using information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a joint design of file caching policy, UAV trajectory, and communication scheduling, which can be viewed as a control system design problem. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper involves distributed caching of files among ground nodes, which can be viewed as a distributed computing problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper focuses on content-centric communication systems, which involve the transmission and retrieval of multimedia files.
